[[File:Kirani James Athletic Stadium, Nov 2016.jpg|thumb]]

'''Police Ground''' is a [[multi-purpose stadium]] in [[St. George's, Grenada|St. George's]], [[Grenada]]. It is currently used mostly for [[football (soccer)|football]] matches.  The stadium holds 10,000 people.

It was renamed to Kirani James Athletic Stadium in April 2017, in honour for the first olympic medallist of Grenada, [[Kirani James]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Grenada: Centre of the Athletic World|url=http://www.nowgrenada.com/2017/04/grenada-centre-athletic-world/|website=NOW Grenada|accessdate=18 June 2017|date=7 April 2017}}</ref>

