[[File:Graham Taylor.jpg|thumb|right|175px|alt=|[[Graham Taylor (footballer)|Graham Taylor]] led Watford to their highest ever league position in 1983.]]
[[Watford Football Club]] are an English [[association football]] club, based in [[Watford]], [[Hertfordshire]]. As of 2016, the team competes in the [[Premier League]], the highest level of the [[English football league system]].

Three managers, [[Len Goulden]], [[Neil McBain]] and [[Malky Mackay]], have taken charge of the club on two separate occasions, while [[Graham Taylor (footballer)|Graham Taylor]] had three stints as manager of the club. The statistics in the following table account for the '''league games''' of each manager.

