{{Infobox newspaper | name = Olé | logo = Diario_ole_logo.png | logo_size = 150px | image = | caption = | type = Daily sports newspaper | format = | owners = [[Grupo Clarín]] | founder = | publisher = | editor = | chiefeditor = | assoceditor = | maneditor = | newseditor = | managingeditordesign = | campuseditor = | campuschief = | opeditor = | sportseditor = | photoeditor = | staff = | foundation = {{Startdate|1996|05|23}} | political = | language = [[Spanish language|Spanish]] | ceased publication = | headquarters = [[Buenos Aires]] | circulation = | sister newspapers = | ISSN = | oclc = | website = {{URL|http://www.ole.com.ar/}} }}
'''''Olé''''' is an Argentine national daily [[sports]] [[newspaper]] published in [[Buenos Aires]], [[Argentina]].
The publication was launched on May 23, 1996, by the [[Clarín (Argentine newspaper)|Clarín Group]]. It has since become the most important sports publication in Argentina, especially since the closing of ''[[El Gráfico]]'' in 2002 (later reopened as a monthly magazine).<ref>[http://www.pagina12.com.ar/diario/deportes/8-2962-2002-03-17.html "El Gráfico" is over] - [[Página/12]] {{es icon}}</ref> Shortly after its establishment, the publication received three awards from the [[Society for News Design]] (1997).<ref>[http://www.snd.org/category/competitions/best-of-news-design/ SND: Archive for the ‘Best of News Design’ Category]</ref>
''Olé'' is mainly focused on [[football (soccer)|football]], but covers most sports events related to Argentina, as well as the most important international sport news.
